# NEXUS — professional tests (scoped)

## Canonical doc

Follow **`NEXUS/docs/PROFESSIONAL-TEST-OUTLINE.md`** for file headers, test IDs (`NX-TEST-…`), and blast-radius notes.

## Where tests live

- **Vitest (pure logic):** `NEXUS/tests/**/*.test.mjs` via `NEXUS/vitest.nexus.config.mjs`.
- **Playwright (smoke):** `NEXUS/e2e/**/*.spec.js` via `NEXUS/playwright.nexus.config.mjs`.

Do not assume a bundler: tests must not import `engine.js` into Node unless you have explicitly mocked WebGL.

## Discipline

- Prefer **one focused assertion group** per test; avoid flaky timing — use `page.waitForSelector` with reasonable timeouts for E2E.
- After security- or URL-related changes, extend **allowlist** unit tests in the same PR.
- Keep **`QA-UPGRADE-MATRIX.md`** / **`docs/QA-MATRIX.md`** in sync when adding a new user-facing flow that needs manual coverage.
